The chairmanship candidate of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) for Bwari Area Council, Shekwogaza John Gabaya, has emerged winner of Saturday’s council polls in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) The Independent National Electoral Commission (INEC) on Sunday declared Gabaya of the PDP winner of Bwari Area Council Chairmanship Election. The INEC’s Returning/Collation Officer for the Bwari Area Council elections, Prof. Amuche Madu, said Gabaya who is the incumbent chairman of the council, polled a total of 13, 045 votes and declared him winner.   NGO to conduct free HIV testing, distributes free condoms in…     Why Nigeria cannot breathe – Yahaya Bello     Benue 2023: I will rescue the state from insecurity, cultism…   Madu said: “Shekwogaza Gabaya of PDP, having certified the requirements of the law and scored the highest number of votes, is hereby declared the winner and is returned elected.” - Advertisement - She also said that the candidate of the All Progressives Congress (APC), Mr Haruna Shekwolo, scored a total of 7,697 votes, while that of the All Progressive Grand Alliance (APGA), Abubakar Abdullahi, scored 603 to come third place. The Bwari Area Council chairmanship elections was conducted in 10 wards of the council namely Igu, Kubwa, Duste, Kawu, Byazin, Shere, Bwari Central, Kuduru and Usuma Wards. The FCT Area Council elections on Saturday held across the 68 wards/constituencies spread across Bwari, Abaji, Gwagwalada, Kuje, Kwali and Abuja Municipal Council (AMAC). A total of 473 candidates sponsored by 14 political parties took part in the elections. SPONSORED